INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (5, N'2148a8de-33bd-436a-a9ab-b734f1d23bd4', 3, 1, N'<p>A2 Films gathers two of the most important labels of independent Brazilian home entertainment, having over 20 years of experience and quality in the distribution of great titles in feature films, documentaries, adult and children&#39;s animations, family productions, musicals and other genres. Located in Alphaville, city of Barueri, S&atilde;o Paulo, A2 Filmes works hard to bring quality content to entertain the whole family, not only the Brazilian ones, but Latin American’s, and provides great entertainment options for the most diverse distribution formats. Present in major international entertainment business markets, the company searches for releases through the world, licensing content that can be distributed in the largest quantity of formats available. We work with cinema products, broad and cable TV, VOD, SVOD and other on-demand channels, as well as physical media such as DVD.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (6, N'e56e6ea8-1ff5-4e51-a116-468c72cf3c11', 3, 2, N'<p>A2 Filmes re&uacute;ne alguns dos mais importantes selos do home entertainment independente brasileiro, somando mais de 20 anos de experi&ecirc;ncia e qualidade na distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o de grandes t&iacute;tulos em longa-metragem de fic&ccedil;&atilde;o, document&aacute;rios, anima&ccedil;&otilde;es adultas e infantis, produ&ccedil;&otilde;es para a fam&iacute;lia, musicais e muito mais. Localizada em Alphaville, na cidade de Barueri, S&atilde;o Paulo, a A2 Filmes trabalha para trazer conte&uacute;do de qualidade para a fam&iacute;lia, n&atilde;o apenas a brasileira, mas da Am&eacute;rica Latina, e fornece &oacute;timas op&ccedil;&otilde;es de entretenimento para os mais diversos formatos de distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o. Presente nos principais mercados de neg&oacute;cios internacionais de entretenimento, nos especializamos em buscar lan&ccedil;amentos nas mais variadas partes do mundo e a licenciar conte&uacute;dos que possam ser distribu&iacute;dos na maior quantidade de formatos dispon&iacute;veis. Trabalhamos com produtos para cinema, TVs aberta e fechada, VOD, SVOD e demais canais on-demand, al&eacute;m de m&iacute;dias f&iacute;sicas, como o DVD. Navegue pelo nosso site e conhe&ccedil;a o que temos para oferecer em nosso cat&aacute;logo. Se a sua empresa busca um fornecedor de conte&uacute;do confi&aacute;vel, comprometido com a qualidade dos produtos que oferece, pode contar com a A2 Filmes!</p>

<p>A Focus Filmes nasceu no segundo semestre de 2005, fruto do trabalho e da uni&atilde;o de tr&ecirc;s profissionais que aliaram seu amor pela S&eacute;tima Arte ao conhecimento do p&uacute;blico brasileiro. Forte no home v&iacute;deo e com muitas op&ccedil;&otilde;es nos g&ecirc;neros favoritos do p&uacute;blico, a distribuidora aposta na diversidade e na tecnologia para alcan&ccedil;ar o consumidor onde ele estiver. Focando no que h&aacute; de mais interessante na tecnologia para o entretenimento dom&eacute;stico mundo afora, a A2 Filmes mant&eacute;m sua tradi&ccedil;&atilde;o de pioneirismo ao trazer para o Brasil o m&aacute;ximo de produtos em Blu-ray e com a op&ccedil;&atilde;o de exibi&ccedil;&atilde;o em 3D, sempre que poss&iacute;vel. O consumidor, &aacute;vido por novidades e em busca de conte&uacute;dos ao seu alcance, a qualquer hora e em qualquer lugar, ganha mais uma op&ccedil;&atilde;o de entretenimento com o portal da A2 Filmes.</p>

<p></p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (7, N'e56ac0f3-7ec5-48de-bc51-5a2ec72f4937', 4, 1, N'<p><strong>The Academia de Filmes has been producing audiovisual entertainment and culture for all screens for 22 years.</strong></p>

<p><strong>More recently, in cinema, he produced "Legalize J&aacute;!", directed by Johnny Ara&uacute;jo and Gustavo Bonaf&eacute;, about the friendship between Marcelo D2 and Skunk and the formation of the band Planet Hemp, consecrated as Best National Feature Film, according to the public, at the 41st S&atilde;o Paulo International Film Festival and with a commercial launch scheduled for 2018. It is in production of the two new feature films by Luiz Fernando Carvalho: "Lost Objects", director&#39;s script in partnership with Jo&atilde;o Paulo Cuenca, and "A Paix&atilde;o segundo GH" based on the eponymous novel by Clarice Lispector. Co-produced "Elis", directed by Hugo Prata, awarded in the categories of best film and actress in various national festivals, such as APCA (Paulista Association of Art Critics).</strong></p>

<p><strong>It also signs "Childhood Clandestine", by Benjam&iacute;n &Aacute;vila - Argentinean nomination for the 2013 Oscar and finalist of the Cinefondation in Cannes. Among other productions for the cinema are: the feature films "Eu te Levo" (2017), by Marcelo M&uuml;ller; Tadeu Jungle&#39;s “Amanh&atilde; Nunca Mais” "(2011), and Paulo Machline&#39;s "Natimorto" (2009), and the documentaries "Tit&atilde;s - a Vida at&eacute; Parece uma Festa” (2009), by Branco Mello and Oscar Rodrigues Alves, and "Hist&oacute;rias do Rio Negro” (2007), by Luciano Cury. Academia de Filmes’ works have been awarded by the Academy of Cinematographic Arts and Sciences of Argentina, the Rio Film Festival, Guadalajara, San Sebastian and Fiesp / Sesi-SP Cinema Awards.</strong></p>

<p><strong>For TV, the company produced, among other works, the micro-series "A Pedra do Reino (TV Globo), based on Ariano Suassuna’s work, directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, and "Love in 4 Acts " (TV Globo); with general direction of Roberto Talma; the macross&eacute;rie "Milagres de Jesus" (Record TV); the series "Nat&aacute;lia" (TV Brasil / Universal Channel); the "200 Degree" docu-realities (Discovery Home & Health), with chef Henrique Foga&ccedil;a, and "Linhas Tortas" (PlayTV); the documentary series "Spirit of the Fight" (Channel Combate) and the reality "Mixados" (PlayTV). For 2018, the premieres of the new seasons of "Natalia" and "Spirit of the Fight" are planned, as well as the unpublished documentary series "Eu te Dedico" (Art 1).</strong></p>

<p><strong>Academia de Filmes also works in advertising, producing over 7,000 films, winning professional recognition and numerous national and international awards, including Cannes Lions, Clio and Fiap. It is also sister company of Base 7, specialized in designing, managing and executing projects of artistic and sociocultural relevance, internationally recognized for its expertise in holding exhibitions, museums, memory preservation programs and cultural heritage.</strong></p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (8, N'a61ecbbb-f73d-476f-897c-a7f549ac0e01', 4, 2, N'<p><strong>A Academia de Filmes produz audiovisual de entretenimento e cultura, para todas as telas, h&aacute; 22 anos.</strong></p>

<p><strong>Mais recentemente, em cinema, produziu “Legalize J&aacute;!”, de Johnny Ara&uacute;jo e Gustavo Bonaf&eacute;, sobre a amizade entre Marcelo D2 e Skunk e a forma&ccedil;&atilde;o da banda Planet Hemp, consagrado como Melhor Fic&ccedil;&atilde;o Nacional, segundo o p&uacute;blico, na 41a Mostra Internacional de Cinema de S&atilde;o Paulo e com lan&ccedil;amento comercial previsto para 2018. Est&aacute; em produ&ccedil;&atilde;o dos dois novos longas-metragens de Luiz Fernando Carvalho: “Objetos Perdidos”, roteiro do diretor em parceria com Jo&atilde;o Paulo Cuenca, e “A Paix&atilde;o segunda GH”, baseado no romance hom&ocirc;nimo de Clarice Lispector.  Coproduziu “Elis”, de Hugo Prata, premiado nas categorias de melhor filme e atriz em diversos festivais nacionais, como APCA (Associa&ccedil;&atilde;o Paulista dos Cr&iacute;ticos de Arte).</strong></p>

<p><strong>Assina ainda “Inf&acirc;ncia Clandestina”, de Benjam&iacute;n &Aacute;vila – indica&ccedil;&atilde;o Argentina ao Oscar 2013 e finalista do Cinefondation, em Cannes. Entre outras produ&ccedil;&otilde;es para o cinema est&atilde;o: os longas-metragens “Eu te Levo” (2017), de Marcelo M&uuml;ller; “Amanh&atilde; Nunca Mais” (2011), de Tadeu Jungle, e “Natimorto” (2009), de Paulo Machline, e os document&aacute;rios “Tit&atilde;s – a Vida at&eacute; Parece uma Festa” (2009), de Branco Mello e Oscar Rodrigues Alves, e “Hist&oacute;rias do Rio Negro” (2007), de Luciano Cury. Temos obras premiadas pela Academia de Artes e Ci&ecirc;ncias Cinematogr&aacute;ficas da Argentina, pelos festivais do Rio, de Guadalajara, de San Sebastian e Pr&ecirc;mio Fiesp/Sesi-SP de Cinema.</strong></p>

<p><strong>Para a TV, a empresa produziu, entre outras obras,  as micross&eacute;ries “A Pedra do Reino (TV Globo), da obra de Ariano Suassuna, dire&ccedil;&atilde;o-geral de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, e “Amor em 4 Atos” (TV Globo); dire&ccedil;&atilde;o-geral de Roberto Talma; a macross&eacute;rie "Milagres de Jesus" (Record TV), dire&ccedil;&atilde;o-geral de Jo&atilde;o Camargo; a s&eacute;rie “Nat&aacute;lia” (TV Brasil/Universal Channel), dire&ccedil;&atilde;o-geral de Andr&eacute; Pellenz; os docu-realities “200 Graus” (Discovery Home & Health), com o chef Henrique Foga&ccedil;a, e “Linhas Tortas” (PlayTV); a s&eacute;rie documental “Esp&iacute;rito da Luta” (Canal Combate) e o reality “Mixados” (PlayTV). Para 2018, est&atilde;o previstas as estreias das novas temporadas de "Nat&aacute;lia" e "Esp&iacute;rito da Luta", al&eacute;m da s&eacute;rie documental in&eacute;dita "Eu te Dedico" (Arte 1).</strong></p>

<p><strong>A Academia de Filmes tamb&eacute;m atua em publicidade, tendo produzido mais de 7 mil filmes, conquistado reconhecimento profissional e in&uacute;meros pr&ecirc;mios nacionais e internacionais, como Cannes Lions, Clio e Fiap. &Eacute; tamb&eacute;m empresa-irm&atilde; da Base 7, especializada em conceber, gerir e executar projetos de relev&acirc;ncia art&iacute;stica e sociocultural, reconhecida internacionalmente pela expertise na realiza&ccedil;&atilde;o de exposi&ccedil;&otilde;es, museus, programas de preserva&ccedil;&atilde;o da mem&oacute;ria e patrim&ocirc;nio cultural.</strong></p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (9, N'008bd943-a871-452a-8049-8023bc0cca66', 5, 1, N'<p>For more than 90 years, we have been working to improve education in Brazil. Our team of educators and communication professionals are continuously using the latest technology to produce quality content that is accessible to all. "Communicating to educate" has been our mission for all these years. Our facilities have all the infrastructure for the production of high definition programs (FHD), with satellite distribution and in multiple platforms (TV, computer, tablet, smartphone and smart TV) by streaming, videos on demand (VoD) among other services that technology, accessibility and educational content. We believe that education is for everyone. For this reason, we are committed to making audiovisual programs (recorded and live) fully accessible, either through LIBRAS (Brazilian Sign Language) and open (or hidden) subtitles for deaf people or through audiodescripts for the blind. Quality programming. Education within the reach of all. Technology, accessibility, inclusion to be worth! Ideas to access and share anytime, anywhere!</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
