<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-size:13.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="color:black">Arte 1 also invests in co-productions and bets on documentaries series that promote national independent production and explore the universe of art as &quot;Geografia da Arte&quot;, &quot;Work in Progress&quot;, &quot;Inven&ccedil;&otilde;es da Alma&quot; and &quot;Artistas Pl&aacute;sticos Brasileiros&quot;.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-size:13.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="color:black">After a premiere in December 2012 on Sky TV and Claro TV, Arte 1 was officially launched in March 2013 by Bandeirantes Comunication Group. Currently, is available in almost all main pay-tv operators and independent ones, which corresponds to over than 12 million subscribers throughout Brazil.</span></span></span></span></span></p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
