INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (39, N'4d87f0a1-9329-4d2f-82d8-9bb7e42915cc', 20, 1, N'<p>Luciana Eguti and Paulo Muppet founded Birdo with 2 computers and a fax machine back in 2005. They now share the roles of producers and directors over a team of&nbsp;multitalented artists that include writers, designers, and animators.</p>

<p>Their films as directors have been awarded in festivals and selected for prestigious publications such as Stash, Pictoplasma, Vimeo Staff Picks and Youtube&#39;s global homepage. As Birdo&#39;s animation directors, Luciana and Paulo worked on more than 80 projects, including 6 feature films, 17 short films and music videos, dozens of commercials for clients such as FIAT, Google and Unilever and many other diverse projects from social games to theater plays. More recently Luciana and Paulo won, together with their team, the contest to create the Olympic and Paralympic Mascots for Rio 2016, Vinicius and Tom.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Luciana and Paulo are the first brazilian artists to give a talk at Pictoplasma in Berlin, the world&#39;s leading conference about character culture.&nbsp;They also lectured at events such as Pixel Show, Latin America&#39;s biggest art and design event, and Animamundi, Brazil&#39;s most important animation festival. In it&#39;s 2015 edition, Animamundi chose Birdo as the first brazilian animation studio to be honored by the festival.</p>

<p>Currently Luciana and Paulo are&nbsp;involved in several projects in production at Birdo, such as the series &ldquo;Oswaldo&rdquo; (TV Cultura, Cartoon Network), &ldquo;Cupcake and Dinosaur&rdquo; (Netflix, Teletoon), Papaya Bull (Nickelodeon), and&nbsp;Star Wars - Forces of Destiny (Disney XD).&nbsp;</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (40, N'45c41be7-ead1-4f5e-98cd-6e606d060b85', 20, 2, N'<p>Luciana Eguti e Paulo Muppet fundaram a Birdo com 2 computadores e uma m&aacute;quina de fax l&aacute; atr&aacute;s em 2005. Hoje eles compartilham os pap&eacute;is de produtores e diretores, liderando uma equipe de artistas multitalentosos que inclui roteiristas, designers e animadores.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Seus filmes como diretores foram exibidos em festivais como Cl&eacute;rmont-Ferrand e Pictoplasma, premiados dentro e fora do Brasil e selecionados para publica&ccedil;&otilde;es de prest&iacute;gio tais como Stash, Vimeo Staff Picks e a home page global do Youtube. Como diretores de anima&ccedil;&atilde;o da Birdo, Luciana e Paulo trabalharam em mais de 80 projetos, incluindo 6 longas-metragens, 17 curtas e videoclipes, dezenas de comerciais para clientes como FIAT, Google e Unilever, al&eacute;m de projetos internacionais diversos que v&atilde;o de proje&ccedil;&otilde;es em massa na Times Square a exposi&ccedil;&otilde;es de arte. Recentemente Luciana e Paulo venceram em conjunto com sua equipe o concurso para a cria&ccedil;&atilde;o dos Mascotes dos Jogos Ol&iacute;mpicos e Paral&iacute;mpicos Rio 2016, Vin&iacute;cius e Tom.</p>

<p>Luciana e Paulo foram os &uacute;nicos brasileiros a palestrar no Pictoplasma, a confer&ecirc;ncia sobre personagens mais importante do mundo. Em 2015 tamb&eacute;m foram palestrantes no Pixel Show e Animamundi, onde a Birdo conquistou o t&iacute;tulo de primeira produtora brasileira homenageada pelo festival.</p>

<p>Atualmente Paulo e Luciana est&atilde;o envolvidos em diversos projetos em produ&ccedil;&atilde;o na Birdo, tais como as s&eacute;ries&nbsp;&ldquo;Oswaldo&rdquo; (TV Cultura, Cartoon Network), &ldquo;Cupcake and Dinosaur&rdquo; (Netflix, Teletoon), Papaya Bull (Nickelodeon), e&nbsp;Star Wars - Forces of Destiny (Disney XD).&nbsp;</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
