INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (139, N'7dc08465-399f-4833-9a55-5c1a9dafb208', 70, 1, N'<p><strong>Entertainment One (eOne)</strong> is a global independent studio that specializes in the development, acquisition, production, financing and sales of entertainment content. The Company’s diversified expertise spans across film, television and music production and sales, family programming, merchandising and licensing, and digital content. Through its global reach and expansive scale, powered by deep local market knowledge, the Company delivers the best content to the world.</p>

<p></p>

<p>Entertainment One’s robust network includes film and television studio The Mark Gordon Company; content creation venture Amblin Partners with Steven Spielberg, DreamWorks Studios, Participant Media, and Reliance Entertainment; leading feature film production and global sales company Sierra Pictures; unscripted television production companies Renegade 83, Paperny Entertainment and Force Four Entertainment; world-class music labels Dualtone Music Group and Last Gang; and award-winning digital agency Secret Location.</p>

<p></p>

<p>eOne Television’s current portfolio of original and third party acquired content now consists of over 35 series and long-form programs commissioned by over 20 different broadcast and cable networks, including series from the Company’s exclusive multi-year distribution agreement for all original scripted series from AMC Networks’ AMC and Sundance Channel. eOne Television delivered over 500 hours of compelling new television last year.</p>

<p></p>

<p>Through its development and production hubs in LA, London, Toronto and Sydney, eOne Television is developing and producing a raft of new series with talented production partners for the UK, US and global marketplace. Current scripted series include: <em>Designated Survivor</em> (ABC) and <em>Conviction</em> (ABC) from The Mark Gordon Company; <em>Ice </em>(AT&T Audience Network), executive produced by Antoine Fuqua; <em>Ransom (</em>CBS/TF1/Shaw), executive produced by Frank Spotnitz; <em>Foreign Bodies</em> (E4/TNT);<em> You Me Her </em>(AT&T Audience Network); and <em>Mary Kills People </em>(Lifetime/Global). Highlights from eOne Television’s development slate include the upcoming drama <em>Sharp Objects</em> (HBO), starring Amy Adams, directed by Jean-Marc Vall&eacute;e and based on the best-selling novel by Gillian Flynn; as well as <em>Havana Quartet </em>(Starz), starring Antonio Banderas and written by Eduardo Machado, based on the popular book series by Cuban novelist Leonardo Padura.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
