INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (221, N'fac685ee-e12c-41e6-92d0-177cb3a0000c', 111, 1, N'<p>Founded in 2012, H2O Films is a distribution company with 100% national capital. Its mission is to maximize the performance of the films it releases, prioritizing Brazilian productions. In a highly competitive market, H2O Films seeks to think each project exclusively. Its differential is the great expertise in marketing and the programming know-how of its team.</p>

<p>In its fifth year of operations, it is already responsible for the distribution of more than 30 films, including national and international titles. Among the international films, it distributed "Ouija”, which snatched over 500,000 spectators in one of its partnerships with Universal Pictures, and "Fallen", the first film of the saga of great success. Among the nationals, H2O Films released "Made in China", directed by Estev&atilde;o Ciavatta and starring Regina Cas&eacute;, with more than 400,000 spectators; “C&aacute;ssia Eller”, by Paulo Henrique Fontenelle, one of the highest-grossing Brazilian documentaries; "Vai Que Cola - O Filme", ??with the biggest national opening box office of 2015, which had an audience of more than 3.2 million spectators; the comedy sequel "Party Crashers 2” (“Os Penetras 2 – Quem D&aacute; Mais?”), by Andrucha Waddington; and the family comedy "An Almost Perfect Uncle" with Marcus Majella, both in 2017.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
