INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (223, N'afb18689-a0a7-46b8-b91a-0588e80558c5', 112, 1, N'<p><strong>HADDOCK FILMS</strong> is feature film,documentary and TV production company, <strong><em>Academy Award</em></strong> 2010 winner, <strong><em>Best Film in Foreign Language</em></strong> (<strong><em>"The Secret In Their Eyes"</em></strong>)</p>

<p>Founded in 2006 in Buenos Aires, Argentina. Its aim is to join to the argentine filmmaking industry supporting to its growth with its creative and productive resources, deepening the bows of collaboration between Argentina, Latinoamerica and Spain and promoting quality projects by developing multilateral joint productions.</p>

<p><strong>HADDOCK FILMS</strong> has made as associate producer the argentine feature-films <strong>"Cheese cake" </strong>(“Cara de queso”) by Ariel Winograd (co-produced with Tres Planos Cine and Tornasol Films), successfully released in theatres; <strong>"City in Heat"</strong> (“Ciudad en celo”) by Hern&aacute;n Gaffet (co-produced with Zona Audiovisual and Tornasol Films), "Pilar Mir&oacute;” Best New Director award in 51st International Week of Cinema of Valladolid (2006), “Prize of the Public” in Mar del Plata and Toulouse International Film Festivals (2007); <strong>“Make it seem an accident”</strong> (“Que parezca un accidente”) directed by Gerardo Herrero, starring by Carmen Maura  and Federico Luppi; and <strong>“Little country”</strong> (“Paisito”), coproduction with Uruguay.</p>

<p>In 2008, <strong>HADDOCK FILMS</strong> produced <strong>“The night runner” </strong>(“El corredor nocturno”), starring by Leonardo Sbaraglia and Miguel &Aacute;ngel Sol&aacute;.</p>

<p>That year, <strong>HADDOCK FILMS</strong> was the main argentinean producer of the film <strong>“The secret in their eyes“</strong> (El secreto de sus ojos”) by Juan Jos&eacute; Campanella, theatrically released in 2009 with huge audience success and extraordinary reception from worldwide critics and festivals, Academy Award winner Best Film in Foreign Language.</p>

<p>In 2009, <strong>HADDOCK FILMS</strong> produced <strong>“Widows on Thursdays” (“</strong>Las viudas de los jueves”) based on the homonimous bestseller by Claudia Pi&ntilde;eiro, Clar&iacute;n Award 2005; and in 2010 finished the production and release of the first movie by the young director Miguel Cohan<strong>, “No retun”</strong> (<strong>Sin retorno</strong>) 3 awards winner in Valladolid and selected to the oficial competition at <em>La Habana Film Festival</em>.</p>

<p>On 2012,<strong> HADDOCK FILMS</strong> premiered Ana Piterbarg’s &Oacute;pera Prima <strong>Everybody has a plan (Todos tenemos un plan) </strong>shooted on spectacular natural scenarios of the Delta del Tigre with the stellar participation of Viggo Mortensen and Soledad Villamil, among a great cast. <strong>Todos tenemos un plan</strong> had an excellent argentine and spanish audience reception and a great international films festivals presence like Toronto and R&iacute;o de Janeiro.</p>

<p>As an associate producer, <strong>HADDOCK FILMS</strong>, premiered on 2013 <strong>Tesis sobre un homicidio</strong>, directed by Hern&aacute;n Goldfrid and starred by Ricardo Dar&iacute;n with an extraordinaire audience success on Argentina.</p>

<p>On 2014 produced and premiered <strong>Betib&uacute;</strong>, directed by Miguel Cohan. A film adaptation of the novel by the same name written by Claudia Pi&ntilde;eiro. Starring Mercedes Mor&aacute;n and Daniel Fanego, it was distributed by Warner Bros with a great audience success.</p>

<p>On 2015 produced and premiered <strong>Eva No Duerme</strong> an international co-production between France, Spain and Argentina, directed by Pablo Ag&uuml;ero, starring an international cast headed by Gael Garc&iacute;a Bernal, Dennis Lavant, Imanol Arias and Daniel Fanego. Winner of the <em>Balance de Oro Pantalla Pinamar</em> and nine awards for the <em>Premios C&oacute;ndor de Plata</em> 2016.</p>

<p>On 2016 produced <strong>At The End of the Tunnel (Al Final del T&uacute;nel)</strong>, directed by Rodrigo Grande, starring Leonardo Sbaraglia, Pablo Echarri and Clara Lago. It was a co-production between Spain and Argentina and distributed internationally by Warner Bros. Premiered on 2016, it was one of the top 5 audience rated of the year.</p>

<p>On 2017 produced <strong>The Desert Bride </strong>(<strong>La novia del desierto)</strong> directed by Cecilia At&aacute;n and Valeria Pivato, <em>Un Certain Regard Official Selection</em> of the <em>Festival de Cannes</em> 2017.</p>

<p>On 2017 also produced <strong>The Last Suit (El ultimo traje)</strong>, directed by Pablo Solarz and co-produced by Patagonik Film Group, Zampa Films and Tornasol Films from Spain. Winner of over <em><strong>20 Audience Awards</strong></em> at International Festivals in the world. </p>

<p>On 2018 produced <strong>Happy Hour</strong> directed by Eduardo Albergaria, a co-production with Urca Filmes from Brasil and winner of the INCAA-ANCINE Price.</p>

<p>On 2018 also produced  <strong>A Twelve Year Night</strong> (<strong>La noche de 12 a&ntilde;os), </strong>directed by Alvaro Brechner, a co-production between France, Spain and Uruguay, selected for Orizzonti Competition at <em>La Biennale di Venezia </em>and Horizontes Latinos at<em> San Sebastian Film Festival.</em>The film won, so far, 8 Awards at the Huelva Film Festival, 3 Awards at El Cairo Film Festival and 5 Audience Awards at International Festivals such as Festival de Huelva, Amiens International Film Festival, and Biarritz International Film Festival. <strong>A Twelve Year Nigth</strong> is the Candidate for Uruguay for Oscar Academy of Hollywood.</p>

<p><strong>As of 2012 he has produced numerous series for TV and digital platforms.</strong></p>

<p></p>

