INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (281, N'45af78fe-595b-4c24-8679-e490cf129af3', 141, 1, N'<p><em>O Som e a F&uacute;ria was created in September 1998. The company is fully dedicated to film production in order to establish a connection with independent arthouse cinema. The quality of its proposals, associated with the development of the individual universes of its authors, are the backbone of this production company.</em></p>

<p><em>It’s feature films have been commercially screened in, among others, France, Germany, United Kingdom, Belgium, Switzerland, Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Mexico, USA and Japan.</em></p>

<p><em>Since 2006, films as THE FACE YOU DESERVE, OUR BELOVED MONTH OF AUGUST, UPRISE, RUINS and THE PORTUGUESE NUN are usually present in Years Best Films lists, in international publications as “Cahiers du Cinema”, “Sight & Sound”, “The Guardian”, “New Yorker”, “New York Times”, “Film Comment” and “Clarin”.</em></p>

<p><em>At the same time, since 2003, O Som e a F&uacute;ria began distributing the work that it has been producing.</em></p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (282, N'6ff58ec5-d1cb-4d93-8c41-83994a83d6c7', 141, 2, N'<p>O Som e a F&uacute;ria foi criada em Setembro de 1998. Dedica-se em exclusivo &agrave; produ&ccedil;&atilde;o cinematogr&aacute;fica, procurando estabelecer um v&iacute;nculo com o cinema de autor e independente. A qualidade das propostas cinematogr&aacute;ficas, associadas ao desenvolvimento do universo singular dos seus autores, s&atilde;o as traves mestras desta Produtora.</p>

<p>As suas longas metragens conheceram estreias comerciais em, entre outros, Fran&ccedil;a, Alemanha, Reino Unido, B&eacute;lgica, Su&iacute;&ccedil;a, Brasil, Argentina, Chile, M&eacute;xico, Estados Unidos e Jap&atilde;o.</p>

<p>Desde 2006, filmes como A CARA QUE MERECES, AQUELE QUERIDO M&Ecirc;S DE AGOSTO, A ZONA, RU&Iacute;NAS, A RELIGIOSA PORTUGUESA, TABU, OGEBO E A SOMBRA e AS MIL E UMA NOITES marcam presen&ccedil;a habitual nas listas de melhores filmes do ano em publica&ccedil;&otilde;es internacionais como “Cahiers du Cinema”, “Sight & Sound”, “The Guardian”, “New Yorker”, “New York Times”, “Film Comment” e “Clarin”.</p>

<p>Em 2003, O Som e a F&uacute;ria iniciou-se na distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o das obras que produz.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (283, N'673eca64-39a1-4ff9-b930-abfe7c9b109f', 142, 1, N'<p>OCEAN FILMS is a TV and cinema production company, founded in 2000, with offices in Rio de Janeiro, S&atilde;o Paulo and Florian&oacute;polis, in Brazil.<br />
During its seventeen years of existence, it achieved an important position both on the national and international markets, after producing commercials for different countries, music videos, documentaries for television and feature films.</p>

<p>It has produced the series &ldquo;Brazil and Portugal &ndash; There and Here&rdquo;, in coproduction with TV Cultura and the Portuguese RTP; the series &ldquo;On Wheels &ndash; Latin America&rdquo;, filmed in five countries, for Turner Broadcasting; and the documentary &quot;Surfing the Amazon&quot;, produced for the German HelliVentures FilmProduktion. Besides that, OCEAN has a solid experience in realities: it has produced the Norwegian version of &ldquo;Amazing Race&rdquo; (Rubicon TV and Storm Adventures), filmed in Brazil, Chile and Argentina. Also, it has produced the Brazilian part of the biggest adventure reality from India &ndash; &ldquo;MTV Roadies 8&rdquo; (Colosceum Media), filmed in S&atilde;o Paulo, Minas Gerais and Rio de Janeiro. In 2014, it produced for TV Globo the section &ldquo;Today is the day to&rdquo;, within the weekly show &ldquo;What will it be&rdquo;. OCEAN&rsquo;s partnership with SetCom originated the 52-minute documentary &ldquo;Built Crooked to Go Straight&rdquo;, which is becoming a ten-episode TV series.</p>

<p>In 2016, it released the feature film &ldquo;Little Secret&rdquo;, based on a true story, which was the official Brazilian nominee for the 2017 Oscars, running for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film. The casting was composed of Brazilian stars such as J&uacute;lia Lemmertz, Maria Flor and Marcello Antony, and the international stars Fionnula Flanagan (from the series &ldquo;Law and Order&rdquo; and Lost) and Errol Shand.</p>

<p>OCEAN is currently working on other important projects, which include the production of the feature &ldquo;Golden Men&rdquo;, to be directed by Mauro Lima.<br />
Now in post-production, there are three documentary TV series: &ldquo;Transamaz&ocirc;nica &ndash; A Road to the Past&rdquo;, produced exclusively for the HBO<br />
Latin America, &ldquo;Blood of the Earth&rdquo; and &ldquo;Crossing Moments&rdquo;. Besides that, the feature documentary &ldquo;Self-Defense&rdquo; is also in post-production.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (284, N'cd8cafb7-0669-4ddd-b72d-bf7eb26b5f69', 142, 2, N'<p>OCEAN FILMS &eacute; uma produtora independente de audiovisual com escrit&oacute;rios no Rio de Janeiro, S&atilde;o Paulo e Florian&oacute;polis, refer&ecirc;ncia em produ&ccedil;&otilde;es internacionais na Am&eacute;rica Latina.</p>

<p>Especializada em servi&ccedil;os de produ&ccedil;&atilde;o h&aacute; mais de 15 anos, recentemente passou a investir em conte&uacute;do pr&oacute;prio de cinema e TV, produzindo para canais como TV Globo, TV Cultura, BoxBrazil, Canal Brasil, Turner Broadcasting, CineBrasil TV, Curta TV!, entre outros.</p>

<p>Em 2016 lan&ccedil;ou o longa-metragem Pequeno Segredo, dirigido por David Schurmann e selecionado para representar o Brasil na categoria Melhor Filme Estrangeiro no Oscar 2017. O filme, baseado em uma hist&oacute;ria real, tem no elenco nomes renomados como J&uacute;lia Lemmertz, Maria Flor e Marcello Antony, al&eacute;m das estrelas internacionas Fionnula Flanagan e Errol Shand.</p>

<p>Atualmente produz a s&eacute;rie documental &ldquo;Transamaz&ocirc;nica - uma estrada para o passado&rdquo; com exclusividade para a HBO e dire&ccedil;&atilde;o de Jorge Bodanzky e Fabiano Maciel.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (285, N'3442a9e0-c096-4d56-a339-83fbf6ba9b92', 143, 1, N'<p>Olhar Distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o was founded in partnership with the Olhar de Cinema - International Film Festival of Curitiba in consonance with its purpose of looking for films that dialogue with contemporaneity.</p>

<p>Our aim is to respect the universe of each film, its colors, its culture, its smiles and to cross borders that limit such fictional and real worlds, and take them to other ways of looking, surrounded by different realities, in order to raise awareness and reflection.</p>

<p>We understand that the moment is for us to look at the plurality of singular realities: We want to hear the story that women want to tell - black, white, transsexual; we want to watch the movie that black people have always wanted to film; show on screen the way the indigenous want to be shown.</p>

<p>And so, in pursuit of the amplitude of other narratives that Olhar Distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o wants mostly films made by women, black people, indigenous and transgender.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (286, N'c6ab078e-ec8d-4b99-ab2f-7ef707c8f00a', 143, 2, N'<p>A Olhar Distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o nasceu em parceria com o Olhar de Cinema – Festival Internacional de Curitiba e em conson&acirc;ncia com seu prop&oacute;sito de buscar filmes que dialogam com a contemporaneidade.</p>

<p>Nosso objetivo &eacute; respeitar o universo pr&oacute;prio a cada filme, suas cores, sua cultura, seus sorrisos e transpor as fronteiras que limitam tais mundos, ficcionais ou reais, e lev&aacute;-los a outros olhares, cercados de realidades distintas, a fim de sensibilizar e provocar a reflex&atilde;o.</p>

<p>Entendemos que o momento &eacute; o de olharmos, tamb&eacute;m, para a pluralidade de realidades singulares: Queremos ouvir a hist&oacute;ria que elas, mulheres, querem contar - negra, branca, transexual; queremos assistir ao filme que os negros sempre desejaram filmar; levar as telas o ind&iacute;gena do jeito que ele quer ser;</p>

<p>E assim, na busca da amplitude de outras narrativas que a Olhar Distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o almeja em especial filmes realizados por mulheres, negros, ind&iacute;gena e transg&ecirc;nero.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
