INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (321, N'ac6f381f-d62b-4641-9a50-9962a4cb903a', 161, 1, N'<p>Founded and directed by Rodrigo Teixeira, RT Features is a international producer of cultural content and entertainment for film and television, based in S&atilde;o Paulo, Brazil. Among other productions, RT produced the feature films O Cheiro do Ralo (2006), Abismo Prateado (2010), Tim Maia (2014), Alem&atilde;o (2014) and the series O Hipnotizador (for HBO Latin America in 2015) and Amor em Quatro Atos (for Rede Globo in 2011).</p>

<p>In the international market, RT Features has produced Frances Ha (2013), Night Moves (2013), Love is Strange (2014), Love (2015), Mistress America (2015) and the recent indie hit The Witch (2016). In 2016, the production company produced and premiered the features films Indignation (2016), adaptation of the eponymous book by Philip Roth, and Little Men (2016). In Brazil, released O Sil&ecirc;ncio do C&eacute;u, produced in Uruguay in 2015, and O Filho Eterno, adaptation of the novel by Christopher Tezza.Now, in 2017, RT Features premiered the international productions Patti Cake$ and Call Me By Your Name at the Sundance Film Festival and released the films O Animal Cordial at the Fantasia International Film Festival and Severina at the Rio Festival. In the same year, produced Ad Astra, James Gray’s new film. </p>

<p>Dedicated to working with young and talented directors since its inception, RT Features has formed a joint venture with Martin Scorsese&#39;s Sikelia Productions, to produce films by emerging filmmakers around the world. The first feature film of this partnership, A Ciambra, debuted in the last edition of the Directors&#39; Fortnight at the Cannes Film Festival.</p>

<p></p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (322, N'c9edab6b-93e1-4c9a-8da9-c4c9ebb8a87c', 161, 2, N'<p>Fundada e dirigida por Rodrigo Teixeira, a RT Features &eacute; uma produtora nacional e internacional de conte&uacute;do cultural e entretenimento para cinema e televis&atilde;o, com base em S&atilde;o Paulo, Brasil. Dentre outras produ&ccedil;&otilde;es, seu curr&iacute;culo conta com os longas-metragens O Cheiro do Ralo (2006), O Abismo Prateado (2010), Tim Maia (2014), Alem&atilde;o (2014) e as s&eacute;ries O Hipnotizador (para a HBO Latin America em 2015) e Amor em Quatro Atos (para a Rede Globo em 2011).</p>

<p>No mercado internacional, a RT Features produziu os longas Frances Ha (2013), Night Moves (2013), Love is Strange (2014), Love (2015),  Mistress America (2015) e o recente sucesso mundial indie The Witch (2016). Em 2016 produziu e estreou os longas-metragens Indignation (2016), adapta&ccedil;&atilde;o do livro hom&ocirc;nimo de Philip Roth e Little Men (2016). No Brasil lan&ccedil;ou O Sil&ecirc;ncio do C&eacute;u, produzido no Uruguai em 2015, e O Filho Eterno, adapta&ccedil;&atilde;o do romance de Crist&oacute;v&atilde;o Tezza. J&aacute; em 2017, a RT Features estreou as produ&ccedil;&otilde;es internacionais Patti Cake$ e Call Me By Your Name no Festival de Sundance e lan&ccedil;ou os filmes O Animal Cordial no Fantasia International Film Festival e Severina no Festival do Rio. No mesmo ano, a RT Features produziu o novo filme de James Gray, Ad Astra.</p>

<p>Dedicada a trabalhar com jovens e talentosos diretores desde a sua cria&ccedil;&atilde;o, a RT Features formou uma joint venture com a Sikelia Productions, de Martin Scorsese, com o objetivo de produzir filmes de cineastas emergentes em todo o mundo. O primeiro longa-metragem desta parceria, A Ciambra, estreou na &uacute;ltima edi&ccedil;&atilde;o da Quinzena dos Realizadores no Festival de Cannes.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.463' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
