INSERT [dbo].[OrganizationDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [OrganizationId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (425, N'629dbd46-8026-48f1-b74e-30a9e37a171a', 213, 1, N'<p>"yes" ,the only multi-channel Satellite TV platform in Israel , was established in 1998, and launched its broadcasts in 2000. "<em>yes</em>" offers hundreds of programs in 4K UltraHD resolution, and carries about 150 video channels, dozens in HD (1080i format), as well as a wide range of radio and music channels.</p>

<p>As the leading content provider in Israel, "<em>yes</em>" is also one of the world&#39;s pioneer platforms in terms of quality, abundance and variety of programming, offering a huge selection targeting a wide and versatile audience. "<em>yes</em>" carries many partner channels, and also produces its own "yes" series, films and documentary channels. The "yes" owned channels, which are market differentiators and constitute the platform&#39;s uniqueness and competitive edge, include: 6 movie channels which air 95% of all theatrical releases in Israel, all offered within a year of their debut; 5 series channels: <em>yes</em> Drama, <em>yes</em> Action, <em>yes </em>Comedy, <em>yes</em> Oh and the flag ship series channel <em>yes</em> Edge, which broadcasts ground breaking series from the US and the world. All <em>yes</em> series channels broadcast award-winning programs Day and Date with worldwide premieres.</p>

<p>"<em>yes</em>" supports and invests in the Israeli creative community and brings to the screen the most buzzed about original award winning productions. The company&#39;s local productions have for many years dominated the Israeli Television Academy Awards in numerous genres: drama, factual, comedy, docu-reality, children and teens. "<em>yes</em>" most recent drama hit "Fauda", hailed by the New York Times as one of the world&#39;s best series for 2017. In the international award circuit "<em>yes"</em> won the top<em> Grand Jury Prize at Series Mania festival in France two years in a row - for "Your Honor" (2017) and "On the spectrum" (2018) ; many of the company&#39;s productions have achieved international recognition, and have been successfully licensed as format and finished tape programs to global television networks and services.</em></p>
