INSERT [dbo].[HoldingDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [HoldingId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (139, N'ae647541-aa3f-42d1-8287-fffba1e278a8', 71, 1, N'<p>Gullane, founded in 1996 by brothers Caio Gullane and Fabiano Gullane, is one of todays&rsquo; best-known and acclaimed Brazilian production companies, having produced over 30 feature films and more than 15 television series. Its productions have been shown at the most prestigious festivals around the world, winning more than 200 awards, as well as being distributed in many countries. A focus on international co-productions is the company&rsquo;s trademark.</p>

<p>Among the company&rsquo;s most highlighted productions are &ldquo;Just Like Our Parents&rdquo; by La&iacute;s Bodanzky, Panorama Special - Berlin 2017, &ldquo;The Second Mother&rdquo;, by Anna Muylaert, Audience Award at Berlin &ndash; Panorama and Best Actress at Sundance 2015; &ldquo;The Violin Teacher&rdquo;, by S&eacute;rgio Machado, Closing Film in Piazza Grande at Locarno 2015; &ldquo;A Wolf at the Door&rdquo;, by Fernando Coimbra, Best Film at San Sebastian &ndash; Horizontes Latinos and Miami 2013 and Official Selection at Toronto; &ldquo;Amazonia 3D&rdquo;, co-production with France by Thierry Ragobert, Closing Film at Venice and Official Selection at Toronto 2013; &ldquo;Rio 2096, a Story of Love and Fury&rdquo;, by Luiz Bolognesi, the Best Film at Annecy 2013; &ldquo;Tabu&rdquo;, co-production with Portugal, Germany and France, by Miguel Gomes, Competition at Berlin 2012; &ldquo;Plastic City&rdquo;, co-production with China / Hong Kong by Yu Likwai, Competition at Venice 2008; &ldquo;Birdwatchers&rdquo;, coproduction with Italy by Marco Bechis, Competition at Venice 2008; &ldquo;The Year My Parents Went on Vacation&rdquo;, by Cao Hamburger, Competition at Berlin 2007 and Oscar Short List; &ldquo;Carandiru&rdquo;, by Hector Babenco, Competition at Cannes 2003; &ldquo;Brainstorm&rdquo;, by La&iacute;s Bodanzky, Official Selection at Toronto and Locarno in 2001.</p>

<p>Gullane has also produced the trilogy &ldquo;Till Luck do Us Part&rdquo;, the top Brazilian box office in 2012, 2014 and 2016.</p>

<p>In 2017 Gullane celebrates a projects lineup with the new exciting films by La&iacute;s Bodanzky, Daniel Rezende, Luiz Bolognesi, Karim A&iuml;nouz, Fernando Coimbra and Cao Hamburger among others.</p>

<p>Besides cinema, Gullane also produces content for TV including series and telefilms for important Brazilian and international broadcasters such as HBO, ESPN, Discovery, Animal Planet and Globo, and in 2012 Gullane inaugurated its distribution branch.</p>

<p>The production company has been chosen to represent Brazil on the Oscar run with two submissions; the first one in 2015 with &lsquo;The Second Mother&rsquo;, and the second one in 2017/2018, with &ldquo;Bingo - The King of The Mornings&rdquo;.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[HoldingDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [HoldingId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (140, N'd16f0bfb-72c9-41f0-a23e-0b141dda29dd', 71, 2, N'<p>Sobre a Gullane</p>

<p>Em 1996, os irm&atilde;os Caio e Fabiano Gullane fundaram a Gullane Entretenimento, hoje somando mais de 40 filmes com destaque no Brasil e no exterior, 20 s&eacute;ries de televis&atilde;o, in&uacute;meros especiais e document&aacute;rios. &ldquo;Carandiru&rdquo;, &ldquo;Bicho de sete cabe&ccedil;as&rdquo;, &ldquo;O ano em que meus pais sa&iacute;ram de f&eacute;rias&rdquo;; a franquia &ldquo;At&eacute; que a sorte nos separe&rdquo;; &ldquo;Que horas ela volta?&rdquo;, &quot;Como nossos pais&rdquo;, &quot;Bingo, O rei das manh&atilde;s&rdquo;; as s&eacute;ries &ldquo;Alice&rdquo; (HBO), Unidade B&aacute;sica (Universal) e &ldquo;Carcereiros &rdquo;(TV Globo) s&atilde;o algumas das obras realizadas pela Gullane nos &uacute;ltimos anos.</p>

<p>Uma produtora ativa no crescimento do audiovisual brasileiro que ancora seus projetos com os melhores talentos e parceiros do entretenimento. Sua capacidade e empenho em todas as etapas de realiza&ccedil;&atilde;o a garantiu importantes coprodu&ccedil;&otilde;es internacionais e a comercializa&ccedil;&atilde;o de suas obras para mais de mais de 60 pa&iacute;ses, levando a identidade do cinema nacional mundo a fora.</p>

<p>Caracterizada por sensibilizar e movimentar reflex&otilde;es atrav&eacute;s de suas hist&oacute;rias a Gullane j&aacute; acumulou mais de 500 pr&ecirc;mios e nomea&ccedil;&otilde;es em sua carreira, al&eacute;m de ter seus projetos reconhecidos nas sele&ccedil;&otilde;es oficiais dos festivais mais importantes do mundo como: Oscar, Cannes, Berlim, Sundance, Toronto, Veneza e o pr&ecirc;mio Emmy.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[HoldingDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [HoldingId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (141, N'ca42ff56-09b8-44eb-87ce-e93542e31cf7', 72, 1, N'<p>Founded in 2012, H2O Films is a distribution company with 100% national capital. Its mission is to maximize the performance of the films it releases, prioritizing Brazilian productions. In a highly competitive market, H2O Films seeks to think each project exclusively. Its differential is the great expertise in marketing and the programming know-how of its team.</p>

<p>In its fifth year of operations, it is already responsible for the distribution of more than 30 films, including national and international titles. Among the international films, it distributed &quot;Ouija&rdquo;, which snatched over 500,000 spectators in one of its partnerships with Universal Pictures, and &quot;Fallen&quot;, the first film of the saga of great success. Among the nationals, H2O Films released &quot;Made in China&quot;, directed by Estev&atilde;o Ciavatta and starring Regina Cas&eacute;, with more than 400,000 spectators; &ldquo;C&aacute;ssia Eller&rdquo;, by Paulo Henrique Fontenelle, one of the highest-grossing Brazilian documentaries; &quot;Vai Que Cola - O Filme&quot;, ??with the biggest national opening box office of 2015, which had an audience of more than 3.2 million spectators; the comedy sequel &quot;Party Crashers 2&rdquo; (&ldquo;Os Penetras 2 &ndash; Quem D&aacute; Mais?&rdquo;), by Andrucha Waddington; and the family comedy &quot;An Almost Perfect Uncle&quot; with Marcus Majella, both in 2017.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
INSERT [dbo].[HoldingDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [HoldingId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (142, N'11ac580e-a68b-424d-926b-ec39691236b3', 72, 2, N'<p>Fundada em 2012, a H2O Films &eacute; uma distribuidora de Cinema com capital 100% nacional. Sua miss&atilde;o &eacute; potencializar ao m&aacute;ximo o desempenho dos filmes que lan&ccedil;a, com prioridade para as produ&ccedil;&otilde;es brasileiras. Em um mercado altamente competitivo, a H2O Films busca tratar e pensar cada projeto de forma exclusiva. Para isso, tem como grande diferencial a expertise em marketing e o know-how em programa&ccedil;&atilde;o de sua equipe.</p>

<p>Em seu quinto ano de atua&ccedil;&atilde;o, j&aacute; &eacute; respons&aacute;vel pela distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o de mais de 30 filmes, incluindo t&iacute;tulos nacionais e internacionais. Dentre os filmes internacionais, distribuiu &ldquo;Ouija &ndash; O Jogo dos Esp&iacute;ritos&rdquo;, em uma de suas parcerias com a Universal Pictures que arrebatou mais de 500 mil espectadores, e o primeiro filme da saga de grande sucesso &ldquo;Fallen&rdquo;. Dentre os nacionais, a H2O Films lan&ccedil;ou &ldquo;Made in China&rdquo;, com dire&ccedil;&atilde;o de Estev&atilde;o Ciavatta e protagonizado por Regina Cas&eacute;, com mais de 400 mil espectadores; C&aacute;ssia Eller, de Paulo Henrique Fontenelle, que, com 72 mil espectadores, um dos document&aacute;rios mais bem-sucedidos de mercado e de cr&iacute;tica; &ldquo;Vai Que Cola - O Filme&rdquo;, com a maior bilheteria de abertura nacional do ano de 2015, que contou com um p&uacute;blico de mais de 3,2 milh&otilde;es de espectadore; a continua&ccedil;&atilde;o da com&eacute;dia de Andrucha Waddington &ldquo;Os Penetras 2 &ndash; Quem d&aacute; mais?&rdquo; e o longa &ldquo;Um Tio Quase Perfeito&rdquo;, com Marcus Majella, ambos em 2017.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1)
