INSERT [dbo].[HoldingDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [HoldingId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (209, N'90bf1145-1172-43bd-876e-ae43630697aa', 106, 1, N'<p>Raccord Produ&ccedil;&otilde;es was founded in 1993 and since then, has accumulated numerous national and international awards.</p>

<p>A active production company in the Brazilian audiovisual market, in it&rsquo;s curriculum more than 20 films between short, medium and feature films, more than 1.000 hours of television content, as well as numerous video-clips of established artists. In recent years, Raccord has also been dedicated to the new platforms, always seeking a convergence of languages and audiovisual devices, developing media for mobile telephony, internet and working on the launch of films in these environments. As an example is the most recent web-series <b>Pra N&atilde;o Chorar</b> and <b>Na Madrugada</b>, both produced in 2013 for the Multishow Channel. Raccord also produced, in 2013, the documentary series for the Bis Channel, entitled <b>Doc Bis</b>.</p>

<p>In 2018 will release it&rsquo;s most recent feature films: <b>Pluft</b>, directed by Rosane Svartman; <b>Running After</b>, directed by Jeferson De, and <b>Mission: Cupid</b>, directed by Rodrigo Bittencourt.</p>

<p>Among the feature films produced are: <b>Os Maias</b> (2015), directed by Jo&atilde;o Botelho &ndash; a Luso-Brazilian co-production that accumulated the bigger box office of a Portuguese film in Portugal; <b>Untangle</b> (2011), directed by Rosane Svartman &ndash; winner of the &ldquo;Best Film&rdquo; award by the Popular Jury of the 9<sup>th</sup> Films Fest Petrobras Brasil, New York (2011); <b>Cartola</b> (2007), directed by L&iacute;rio Ferreira and Hilton Lacerda; <b>Cafun&eacute;</b> (2006), directed by Bruno Vianna; <b>Minha Vida de Menina</b> (2004), directed by Helena Solberg &ndash; winner of the awards for &ldquo;Best Feature Film&rdquo;, &ldquo;Best Film&rdquo; by the Popular Jury, &ldquo;Best Screenplay&rdquo;, &ldquo;Best Cinematography&rdquo;, &ldquo;Best Art Direction&rdquo; and &ldquo;Best Soundtrack&rdquo; at Gramado Film Festival (2004; <b>Once Again Love</b> (2005), directed by Rosane Svartman; <b>Separations</b> (2002), directed by Domingos de Oliveira; <b>The Little Prince&rsquo; Rap Against the Wicked Souls</b> (2000), directed by Paulo Caldas and Marcelo Luna &ndash; winner of the &ldquo;Popular Jury&rdquo; and &ldquo;Renewal in Language&rdquo; awards at the V &Eacute; Tudo Verdade Festival (2000) and &ldquo;Best Film&rdquo; by the International Film Jury (Glauber Rocha Award) at the Day of Cinema of Bahia; and <b>How To Be Single in Rio</b> (1998), directed by Rosane Svartman &ndash; winner of the &ldquo;Special Jury Prize&rdquo; and &ldquo;Best Actor&rdquo; at the Brasilia Film Festival (1997) and &ldquo;Best Film&rdquo; by the Popular Jury at the 1998 Miami Film Festival.</p>

<p>Among the television projects we can find <b>Series C</b> (2017), directed by Samir Abujamra and exhibited at TV Brazil channel; <b>The Songs of my Life</b> (2017), directed by Bruno Levinson and exhibited at Canal Curta! channel; <b>Quero Ser Solteira </b>(2012), exhibited at Multishow Channel; <b>Untangle It</b> (2011 &ndash; 2012), exhibited at Multishow Channel; <b>Note 10</b>, exhibited at Futura Channel; <b>Claro Q &Eacute; Rock</b>, exhibited at Multishow Channel; <b>When We Were Virgins</b>, exhibited at the GNT channel; among others.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1)
