INSERT [dbo].[HoldingDescriptions] ([Id], [Uid], [HoldingId], [LanguageId], [Value], [IsDeleted], [CreateDate], [CreateUserId], [UpdateDate], [UpdateUserId]) VALUES (245, N'29ef3aa3-3beb-4db0-a2d3-17b2ba4b4f11', 124, 1, N'<p><b>Spring Films is a twice Oscar nominated, Emmy, BAFTA, Peabody, Grierson and RTS award winning factual production company based in central London. We specialize in high-end feature documentaries, series, factual entertainment and new media content. Spring is represented by ICM Partners in the US.</b></p>

<p>CEO, Andr&eacute; Singer was Chief Editor of Granada Television&rsquo;s (now ITV) iconic Disappearing World series during the 1980s. In the 1990s he founded the award-winning BBC documentary strand Fine Cut (now Storyville). Andr&eacute; has been responsible for several hundred hours of factual programs for the international TV market and Producer or Executive Producer on fifteen films with Werner Herzog.</p>

<p>Managing Director and Executive Producer, Richard Melman, was Producer and Director of &lsquo;Cold War&rsquo;, a BAFTA nominated and Peabody award-winning 24 part series for CNN. He was Head of Production for Jeremy Isaacs Productions before becoming Channel Director and Executive Director for Artsworld (Now Sky Arts). Richard was the Channels Director and Head of Programming for History, Bio, Military History, The Crime &amp; Investigation Network in Europe, Africa and the Middle East for eight years.</p>

<p>Spring Films recent highlights include: Joshua Oppenheimer&rsquo;s Oscar nominated <b>The Look of Silence</b>, Andre Singer&rsquo;s Emmy winning <b>Night Will Fall </b>&ndash; seen by over 45 million people, Werner Herzog&rsquo;s Emmy nominated Netflix documentary <b>Into The Inferno</b>, the Emmy nominated <b>City 40</b> and <b>A Mother Takes Her Son To Be Shot</b> which recently premiered at the London Film Festival.&nbsp;</p>

<p>This year, Spring Films was nominated for 4 Emmy Awards and we&rsquo;re currently in production on a three part series for Channel 4 and a feature documentary <b>Meeting Gorbachev</b> by Werner Herzog.</p>
', 0, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1, CAST(N'2019-08-09 13:30:17.423' AS DateTime), 1)
GO
